Enum FormulaParserLL3.LOG_BEHAVIOR

    Enclosing class:
    FormulaParserLL3

    public static enum FormulaParserLL3.LOG_BEHAVIOR
extends java.lang.Enum<FormulaParserLL3.LOG_BEHAVIOR>
    Defines the different behaviors the parser can have regarding the 'log' operator.

    By default, it will be read as the natural logarithm 'ln' as it was defined in SBML Level 1, Appendix C, table 6.

    Author:
    rodrigue

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      LOG_IS_LN
      'log' is interpreted as the natural logarithm 'ln' as it was defined in SBML Level 1, Appendix C, table 6.
      LOG_IS_LOG10
      'log(x)' is interpreted as 'log10(x)' or 'log(10, x)'
      LOG_IS_LOG2
      'log(x)' is interpreted as 'log(2, x)'
      LOG_IS_NOT_ALLOWED
      'log(x)' is not allowed and a ParseException will be returned if it is encountered.
